\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \ul \ulc0 MATLAB Plotting
\b0\fs24 \ulnone \
\
1) 
\b \ul Two Dimensional Graph
\b0 \ulnone : To draw a regular two dimensional graph, the following functions should be used in order:\
\
A) 
\f1\b\fs28 plot (X_Var,Y_Var,'Color Marker and/or Line')
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\
This function is used to plot 
\b Y_Var
\b0  against 
\b X_Var
\b0 . The options, 
\f1\b\fs28 Color
\f0\b0\fs24  and 
\f1\b\fs28 Marker and/or Line
\f0\b0\fs24  are used to determine the color and type of the marker and/or line.\
\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural

\b\fs28 \cf0 \ul Very Important
\b0 \ulnone : \cf2 The graph can be plotted by using \ul both Marker and Line\ulnone  or only one of them.
\fs24 \cf0 \
\
-- \ul Choices for Color\ulnone : 
\f1\b\fs28 b
\f0\b0\fs24  (blue), 
\f1\b\fs28 g
\f0\b0\fs24  (green), 
\f1\b\fs28 k
\f0\b0\fs24  (black), 
\f1\b\fs28 r
\f0\b0\fs24  (red), 
\f1\b\fs28 w
\f0\b0\fs24  (white), 
\f1\b\fs28 y
\f0\b0\fs24  (yellow), and etc.\
\
-- \ul Choices for Marker\ulnone : 
\f1\b\fs28 o
\f0\b0\fs24  (circle), 
\f1\b\fs28 d
\f0\b0\fs24  (diamond), 
\f1\b\fs28 +
\f0\b0\fs24  (plus), 
\f1\b\fs28 .
\f0\b0\fs24  (point), 
\f1\b\fs28 *
\f0\b0\fs24  (star)\
\
-- \ul Choices for Line\ulnone : 
\f1\b\fs28 --
\f0\b0\fs24  (dashed), 
\f1\b\fs28 -
\f0\b0\fs24  (solid), 
\f1\b\fs28 -.
\f0\b0\fs24  (dash dot), 
\f1\b\fs28 :
\f0\b0\fs24  (dotted)\
\
B) 
\f1\b\fs28 axis ([Min_X_Axis, Max_X_Axis, Min_Y_Axis, Max_Y_Axis])
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\
This function is used to determine the ranges of X and Y axes. It is helpful to place the plot in the Figure without losing any border of it.\
\
C) 
\f1\b\fs28 xlabel ('X_String')
\f0\b0\fs24   and  
\f1\b\fs28 ylabel ('Y_String')
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\
These two functions specify the names of X and Y axes.\
\
D) 
\f1\b\fs28 title ('Graph's Title')
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\
This function specifies the title of the graph.\
\
2) 
\b Clear Figure Window
\b0 : The function 
\f1\b\fs28 clf
\f0\b0\fs24  is used to clear the Figure Window.\
\
3) 
\b Figure Number
\b0 : The function, 
\f1\b\fs28 figure(n)
\f0\b0\fs24  is used to to determine the index (or number) of a figure (= Figure N). To obtain more information about 
\f1\b\fs28 figure
\f0\b0\fs24  function, refer to cases 
\b 13
\b0  and 
\b 14
\b0 .\
\
4) 
\b Freeze and Unfreeze Figure
\b0 : The functions, 
\f1\b\fs28 hold on
\f0\b0\fs24  and 
\f1\b\fs28 hold off
\f0\b0\fs24  are used to freeze and unfreeze the current graph on the Figure Window.\
\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural

\b \cf0 Important
\b0 : \ul It is useful for having multiple graphs on one Figure Window\ulnone .\
\
5) 
\b Plot Name
\b0 : The function, 
\f1\b\fs28 legend()
\f0\b0\fs24  is used to assign \ul Name\ulnone  or \ul String\ulnone  to each of the showing plots. They are shown in a particular box.\
\
Example: 
\f2\fs28 legend ('String for Plot 1','String for Plot 2')
\f0\fs24 \
\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural

\b\fs28 \cf0 \ul Very Important
\b0 \ulnone : \cf2 The characteristics and positions of \ul Labels\ulnone , \ul Titles\ulnone , \ul Legend\ulnone , and etc. can be modified by going to the "
\b \cf2 Properties
\b0 \cf2 " of the \ul Figure Window\ulnone .
\fs24 \cf0 \
\
6) 
\b Bar Chart
\b0 : The function, 
\f1\b\fs28 bar (X_Var,Y_Var)
\f0\b0\fs24  plots bar chart.\
\
7) 
\b subplot Function
\b0 : It is used to draw multiple plots in one Figure Window. In other words, it makes a matrix of plots.\
\
\ul Format\ulnone : 
\f1\b\fs28 subplot (Row,Column,Index) , plot (argument(s))
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\
\ul Notice\ulnone : For 
\f1\b\fs28 subplot
\f0\b0\fs24  function, the order of indexing is 
\b row-wise
\b0 .\
\
8) 
\b \ul Three Dimensional Graph
\b0 \ulnone : Most of the built-in functions of two dimensional graph category are available for three dimensional graph category too:\
\
\ul Example\ulnone : 
\f1\b\fs28 plot3 (X_Var,Y_Var,Z_Var)
\f0\b0\fs24   or  
\f1\b\fs28 bar3 (X_Var,Y_Var,Z_Var)
\f0\b0\fs24   or  
\f1\b\fs28 zlabel ('Z_String')
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\
A) 
\f1\b\fs28 plot3 (X_Var,Y_Var,Z_Var)
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\
This function plots lines and points in three dimensional space:\
\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural

