9) 
\b Scale of Axes
\b0 : The following functions can be used to change the scale of axes:\
\
A) 
\f1\b\fs28 loglog (X_Var,Y_Var)
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\
It uses logarithmic scales for both X and Y axes.\
\
B) 
\f1\b\fs28 semilogy (X_Var,Y_Var)
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\
It uses a linear scale for X axis and a logarithmic scale for Y axis.\
\
C) 
\f1\b\fs28 semilogx (X_Var,Y_Var)
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\
It uses a logarithmic scale for X axis and a linear scale for Y axis.\
\
10) 
\b Histogram Chart
\b0 : It draws histogram chart according to \ul the frequency of each element\ulnone  (the number of times that it is repeated).\
\
\ul Format\ulnone : 
\f1\b\fs28 hist (Vector)
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\
11) 
\b Pie Chart (Circle Shape Chart)
\b0 : It draws circle chart according to \ul the percentage that each element has\ulnone  in the whole sum.\
\
\ul Format\ulnone : 
\f1\b\fs28 pie (Vector)
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\
12) 
\b MeshGrid
\b0 : This function gets two (or three) vectors and generates two (or three) matrices according to their data in grid plane. It means that it produces \ul all of the possible permutations of the data of vectors\ulnone  in \ul Matrix format\ulnone .\
\
\ul Format\ulnone : 
\f1\b\fs28 meshgrid (X_Vector,Y_Vector,Z_Vector)
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\
13) 
\b Creating Figure Graphics Object
\b0 : It is used to create figure graphics object. Figure objects are the \ul individual windows\ulnone  on the screen in which MATLAB displays \ul graphical outputs\ulnone .\
\
\ul Command\ulnone : 
\f1\b\fs28 figure('Property_Name',Property_Value)
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\
It creates a new figure object using the values of the properties specified.\
\

\f1\b\fs28 Property_Name
\f0\b0\fs24  Sample: 
\f1\b\fs28 Position
\f0\b0\fs24  --> It shows the location and size of the figure.\
\
Its 
\f1\b\fs28 Property_Value
\f0\b0\fs24 : A 4-Element Vector named 
\f1\b\fs28 SceenSize
\f0\b0\fs24 , which is 
\f1\b\fs28 [Left,Bottom,Width,Height]
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural

\b \cf0 \ul For the vector
\b0 \ulnone , 
\f1\b\fs28 Left
\f0\b0\fs24  and 
\f1\b\fs28 Bottom
\f0\b0\fs24  are 
\b Zero (0)
\b0  for all Units except \ul Pixels\ulnone . For Pixels, they are 
\b One (1)
\b0 .\
\
The 
\f1\b\fs28 Width
\f0\b0\fs24  and 
\f1\b\fs28 Height
\f0\b0\fs24  are the \ul screen dimensions\ulnone  in units specified by the units property.\
\

\b \ul Important
\b0 \ulnone : The units that are used for the elements of a vector can be:\
\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Pixels
\f0\b0\fs24 , 
\f1\b\fs28 Normalized
\f0\b0\fs24 , 
\f1\b\fs28 Inches
\f0\b0\fs24 , 
\f1\b\fs28 Centimeters
\f0\b0\fs24 , 
\f1\b\fs28 Points
\f0\b0\fs24 , 
\f1\b\fs28 Characters
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\
All of these units are measured from the \ul lower-left corner\ulnone  of the screen.\
\
